conclusions.bias_mitigation: Code-level bias (AST usage of Protected attributes) was reduced from 1.0 to 0.0 across all mitigation runs. This confirms prompt-level instructions ARE effective for logic exclusion.
conclusions.string_echoing: v2 (strict 'no explanation') was most effective at eliminating prompt leakage (echo rate: 0.067 vs 0.6+ in others).
conclusions.validity_bottleneck: ValidityRate (0.4) remains the primary success gate failure. The model frequently fails to generate valid syntax or follow extraction heuristics regardless of constraint relaxation.
